entry.title: Acaena echinata
entry.content: ID feature of echinata is glabrous leaves except for hairy main vein(s) on lower surface. Then fruit spines are all approximatelythe same length and stems are glabrous-sparsely hairy.

entry.title: Geranium solanderi var. solanderi s.s.
entry.content: Petals deep pink with retuse apex. Anthers with purple/dark dehiscence lines. Sepals with (relatively) long mucro. Long spreading hairs. A few plants found in two locations among 1000s of Geranium retrorsum. Location approximate.

entry.title: Geranium solanderi s.l., Geranium solanderi var. solanderi s.s.

entry.title: Acanthiza chrysorrhoa
entry.content: Looks like Yellow-rumped Thornbill but I didn't see the distinctive yellow rump in flight? White chest is most noticeable feature in flight. In Acacia paradoxa - about 50m between shrubs on this site.

entry.title: Anthus novaeseelandiae
entry.content: Grassland site up for development by Council, which will wipe out this ground-nesting bird. I've not even seen them at Evans St Grassland. I disturbed this bird after unknowingly getting 2m from nest (pretty much invisible) and I still didn't find nest!
